    "contribution_claims": [
      "CoI-based spectral feature grouping recovers planted synergistic modules on synthetic data",
      "Module-guided oblique splits produce different arity than random oblique splits",
      "Unsigned spectral clustering often matches or exceeds signed SPONGE -- important negative result",
      "Binning-based CoI estimator produces all-negative values for some datasets",
      "CoI computation is tractable at moderate dimensionality"
    ],
    "assumptions": [
      "Pairwise CoI sufficiency -- synergistic pairs have most negative CoI",
      "Structural balance -- CoI graphs have balanced signed structure",
      "KSG estimator accuracy -- experiments used binning instead of KSG",
      "Computational tractability O(d^2 * n)",
      "Target benchmark coverage (d<=1000, n<=100K)"
    ],
    "limitations": [
      "CoI computed on subsampled data -- min(n, 20000) or min(n, 10000), not full dataset",
      "Maximum dimensionality gap: real data max d=54 (jannis), far below d<=1000 aspiration. Only synthetic tested d=200",
      "Single regression dataset (california_housing); all others classification. Regression generalization unvalidated",
      "All experiments used quantile binning, not hypothesized KSG estimator. Significant deviation from plan",
      "Higher-order interactions never tested; pairwise CoI assumption unchallenged",
      "No EBM/GA2M baseline despite investigation plan calling for it",
      "SPONGE auto-k instability: often picks wrong k (e.g. k=2 or k=3 instead of true k=4 or k=8)"
    ]
