          "input": "{\"section\": \"motivation\"}",
          "output": "The hypothesis proposed that signed spectral clustering on Co-Information graphs would recover synergistic feature modules better than alternatives, enabling more interpretable oblique decision trees with lower split arity. Four experiments spanning synthetic module recovery, real benchmark comparison, frustration-correlation meta-analysis, and scalability testing were conducted to test this claim systematically.",
          "eval_section_completeness": 1.0
