        {
          "input": "{\"section\": \"what_worked\"}",
          "output": "CoI-based feature grouping successfully identifies planted synergistic modules on synthetic data: SPONGE oracle achieves Jaccard=1.0 on easy/medium variants (SC1 mean Jaccard=0.5565). The pipeline is computationally tractable (SC4: CONFIRMED), with the full 8-dataset benchmark completing in 1679s and highdim d=200 CoI in 116.6s. All methods significantly outperform random partition on structured synthetic data. Pairwise CoI correctly identifies synergistic feature pairs with negative values across all structured variants.",
          "eval_section_completeness": 1.0
        },
        {
          "input": "{\"section\": \"what_didnt_work\"}",
          "output": "Three key findings challenge the hypothesis: (1) The frustration-oblique correlation is non-significant (rho=-0.108, p=0.714, bootstrap 95% CI=[-0.678, 0.527]), thoroughly disconfirming the predictive utility of frustration index. (2) Unsigned spectral clustering matches or exceeds signed SPONGE on most metrics (unsigned mean Jaccard=0.5989 vs SPONGE oracle=0.5565), undermining the claimed advantage of signed spectral methods. (3) On real benchmarks, signed spectral vs random oblique: mean accuracy delta=-0.0067, mean arity delta=2.1825, win rate=42.50% (SC2 verdict: PARTIALLY_CONFIRMED).",
          "eval_section_completeness": 1.0
        },
        {
          "input": "{\"section\": \"reframed_story\"}",
          "output": "The core contribution is the CoI -> spectral clustering -> oblique split pipeline itself as a principled feature grouping mechanism, even if signed spectral does not outperform unsigned. The negative result on signed vs unsigned is valuable: it demonstrates that the additional complexity of signed spectral methods (SPONGE) is not justified by the data. The binning-based CoI estimator bias discovery is a methodological finding relevant to the broader PID/CoI community. The pipeline's computational tractability and synthetic validation provide a solid foundation for future work with improved estimators.",
          "eval_section_completeness": 1.0
        },
        {
          "input": "{\"section\": \"future_directions\"}",
